projects: [{'title': 'globalDrive Africa - aCar Mobility Research Project', 'date': {'start': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}, 'end': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}}, 'description': "The objective of the aCar Mobility research project is to find sustainable solutions addressing access to mobility for the transport of people, goods and equipment in rural areas in Sub-Saharan Africa. It is funded by the German Ministry of Economic Cooperation and International Development (BMZ) and supported by the German Agency for International Cooperation (GIZ). The research project collaborates closely with the Ivorian Technical University l'Institut National Polytechnique - Félix Houphouët-Boigny (INP-HB) in the capital Yamoussoukro.
